Description: Ring foot with turn of wall of Attic(?) pottery skyphos; interior glazed streaky black; exterior: painted rays at base of wall, "echoed" on edge of foot below; reserved: resting surface and underside with central dot and circle and bands at outside; inscription cut on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 483)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.116)
